lized medium is also longer, and in some cases,\ncomparable to the characteristic interval between supernova explosions. Our\nmodels, can successfully explain the near-infrared excesses found in the star\nclusters observed in M33 (Rela\\~no et al. 2016) assuming a low heating\nefficiency and mass-loading. In this scenario, the presence of the NIR-MIR\nexcess is an indication of efficient dust production in SNe and its subsequent\ndestruction\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 May 2017 18:00:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-07-27"}
